The new issue will also be available for sale in the magazine's Microstores, apps and applets, as well as the first business APP.

Read on for more on the logistics and logistics of getting back to work

The resumption of work by the State Post Bureau may be more of a gesture to the concrete and minor aspects of the distribution process, and the shortage of young men is still a problem that can not be solved in the short term.

Reporter | Deng Shuxia and Liu Pingting

Editor | Rui Chen

The timeliness of logistics and local distribution used to be one of China's proudest business indicators, but the mature logistics system, which has been in operation for years, is experiencing a rare labour shortage.

Starting Feb. 1, Jiuye, a fresh produce supply chain service in Shanghai, has introduced a large number of new drivers from the restaurant industry to its logistics partners. Before taking up their duties, these new drivers need to undergo a half-hour "crash course" to understand the general distribution process of the fresh supply chain. Some more specific operational details, can only be encountered in the actual transport process through live broadcast or look at the operation manual and so on.

"This is a special case under special circumstances. In the past, our training process for drivers was relatively rigorous and complicated, and we had to take examinations before we could take up our positions,"Ma Yujun, general manager of the fresh transportation division of Jiuye supply chain, told Yimagazine.

Spring Festival holiday so far, affected by the epidemic, fresh e-commerce appeared in the whole industry's single-volume explosion of growth, which brought huge pressure to the supply chain. In the past, it was enough for the carriers of the jiuye supply chain to keep one tenth of their drivers as capacity during the Spring Festival, but this year, the problems of adjusting the pace of the supply chain and the difficulty of drivers returning to work have compounded, even though nearly 50 temporary new drivers have been recruited, the transport capacity of Jiuye has only recovered to about 40% of the normal period.

On February 10, the State Post Bureau announced that 13 postal and delivery companies, including China Post, SF express, jd.com logistics, suning logistics and Santong Yida, had resumed their operations on the same day. However, the official resumption of work may be more like a statement. When it comes to concrete and small distribution links, the shortage of younger brothers is still a problem that can not be solved in the short term, because either they can not successfully return to the big city, or return to a prescribed "quarantine" for a few days.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
SF Express is one of the earliest resumed postal and delivery enterprises.

FRESH AND TAKE-OUT: Rewards pull new, share staff

The business of Jiuye supply chain mainly involves the storage, transportation and distribution of fresh products. According to the original plan, Jiuye supply chain has already planned the customer's car demand before the Spring Festival, and the number of cars used each day has also been arranged. But the outbreak led to a sharp increase in fresh e-commerce unit, the driver is unable to temporary re-work, which has brought great challenges to the supply chain and fresh e-commerce logistics transportation.

According to data provided by the Jiuye supply chain to Yimagazine, demand for Jiuye's customers -- Foshan, jd.com and Tmallon -- Rose 100 times over the past year, there are some of their own logistics transport capacity can not keep up with the supply of new customers.

"Some clients have made business changes during the epidemic, such as restocking one truck per day, but changes in the front-end business model may result in three trucks per day. The sudden increase in the volume of goods is not planned, sometimes two hours in advance of the sudden need for cars,"Ma said.

Lack of manpower is the biggest problem. The JIUYE supply chain has only two local colleagues in Wuhan, who are mainly responsible for the export and import of donated materials, and can not provide support for commercial operations, while only 40 percent of drivers in Beijing, Shanghai and other regions return to work, overall capacity has only recovered to about 70% .

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Fresh enterprise distribution staff is insufficient, single distribution task is heavy.

In order to solve the problem of returning to work, Jiuye supply chain not only uses the way of increasing revenue by 30% to 50% to motivate drivers, but also takes the initiative to contact some drivers who used to do food and beverage delivery. During the outbreak, the catering business almost shut down, some drivers into a non-trading state, Jiuye called on them to temporarily join the fresh industry, become a cold chain transport drivers.

Fresh cold chain transportation not only involves the urban trunk, but also the nearest distance from consumers three kilometers of home delivery service, which is a challenge for fresh e-commerce enterprises.

Many recent in the box Ma Xiansheng, Ding Dong shopping platform orders of consumers, will find that the delivery time usually takes more than 4 hours. In a written response to the report, Yimagazine said that during the Spring Festival, the company retained 75 percent of its total front-line staff, including delivery boys, front-store sorting staff and packaging staff. On January 22, Ding Dong was buying vegetables when he realized that demand would continue to put pressure on supply and logistics. Therefore encourages the vacation staff to come back to work, and encourages the staff to introduce the family and friends to join, each introduction successful one, the staff may obtain 1,200 yuan to 2,000 yuan reward.

In addition, fresh e-commerce has also been "sharing staff. ".

On February 3, Hema and other restaurant brands, such as Yunhaiyao, Xibei, Tanyu and youth restaurant, reached a "shared staff" cooperation. As of February 10,32 companies, including restaurants, hotels and cinemas, have joined Hema, the program covers more than 1,800 people.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Beijing, a box Ma Xiansheng store, sharing the staff in the warehouse tally.

Ding Dong also seeks to buy food with restaurants, hotels and other service-oriented enterprises, has more than 400 employees to join its first-line jobs, the overall plan is said to recruit about 1,500 people.

"there are 10 shared employees in the store and more will follow. We need more staff in our inner warehouse, and sharing staff can meet the operational needs,"Jumez, director of Beijing International Trade Century Fortune Center, told Yimagazine.

Wang Zixuan, from Yunhaiyao, was one of the 10. Before that, he was head of Yunhaiyao's front office. Wang stayed in Beijing during the holiday, and about two weeks ago, he received an e-mail from the company about his work with Hemaxiansheng. "At that time, there were about 200 applicants, all of whom had been in Beijing but had not returned to their hometown. They were later screened for ages 18 to 45, and the pass rate was quite high, " Wang said.

On February 4, Wang Zixuan arrived at the store of he Ma Xiansheng and began tallying and inventory after 2 hours of business training. He did not say how much he would be paid or how long he would work each day.

In terms of distribution, Harvard is trying a "more direct" solution -- Foshan, in partnership with carrier, sends cars to the community and places them there. Compared with the battery car, such a single delivery capacity can be 2-3 times higher, and more can achieve "contactless distribution. ". Since February 8, Shanghai Dazhong Travel, Caixin United Auto Rental (Beijing) Co. , Ltd. and 1919 Liquor Platform Technology Co. , Ltd. have also announced nationwide employment cooperation with Hema, covering Beijing, Guangzhou, Shanghai, Chengdu and other cities, the current pilot area to have parking conditions mainly stores.

At the same time, the impact of the epidemic on the physical catering industry also spread directly to the delivery industry, where ele.me and Meituan even declined an official interview with First Business Magazine Yimagazine.

"Only two of the more than 100 takeout vendors I work for are still open, " a Meituan takeout manager in Beijing told China Business News Yimagazine, whose district recently saw a confirmed case of new pneumonia, most restaurants are banned, and those that can be opened have been told not to entertain groups of more than three people or they will be deemed to be "eating together" .

In addition to the finished products, many restaurants are also exploring more ways to boost their business. For example, Yunhaiyao is developing a community-and supply-chain-based "door-to-door selling" business, with service stations located within a three-kilometer radius of the store, to provide services for the purchase of food raw materials and semi-finished products for the residents.

Another delivery man in Beijing said he planned to return to Beijing within the next two days to prepare for the resumption of work after the quarantine. "I was lucky enough to go home years ago. Some of my colleagues stayed in Beijing for the Chinese New Year and could earn 600 or 700 yuan a day before the new year. But there weren't many orders to take in this half-month. They didn't get much bonus pay, and they couldn't buy masks. Now they all regret it and might as well go home for the New Year. "

Delivery boy: The list and income are less, but busier

Epidemic superposition of the traditional off-season Spring Festival, so that the goods labradors suffered a sharp drop in orders.

"after all, people are afraid to go out, businesses are closed and traffic is controlled. Our business volume dropped by 93 percent during the Spring Festival and the epidemic, and was only 7 percent before the epidemic, " Zhou Shengfu, the founder and CEO of Hurla, told Yimagazine.

February 8 Cargo Lala launched the "new champion pneumonia driver protection plan" , as long as the driver in February 83 months before the completion of an order can be claimed. In the event of death due to infection with COVID-19, the family will receive 500,000 yuan from the driver care fund. "I fully understand the concerns of the drivers who are still working on the front line under the epidemic and the concerns of their families. For many drivers' families, the drivers are the backbone and the support of a family, " Zhou said.

Similar epidemic protection funds have also been set up by express delivery companies such as ZTO and YTO.

According to a 2019 State Post Bureau report on the number of couriers, 76.31 percent of couriers were from the countryside, 15.89 percent were from counties and only 7.8 percent were from cities.

This structure means that even though many cities have introduced epidemic prevention and control regulations one after another, requiring communities not to arbitrarily restrict the resumption of work and delivery services in industries such as express delivery and takeout, couriers want to return to work smoothly from their hometown, it's still not easy. Both CAINIAO and Jd.com declined to be interviewed about the resumption of work.

"there used to be five people in our group, but now it's just me and another colleague on duty. The rest of us are either stuck in the village or isolated in the community and are not allowed to go to work, " Zhao told YiMagazine, he has worked in the courier industry for nearly 20 years and is now in charge of the courier collection for China Post and Zhongtong in a region of Haidian District.

Compared with other "three links and one reach" counterparts, Zhao Zhixiong is lucky. He has personal connections at minimum wage, which he can get if he delays returning to work. China Post has set the resumption time for its staff to return to work on February 3, the tenth day of the first lunar month. However, in order to serve customers earlier, he returns to Beijing from Hebei around the Sixth Day of the first lunar month every year, so it was in Florida this year, when Beijing didn't have as tight a grip on those who arrived from other parts of the country.

ZTO will resume work on Feb. 10, and many colleagues who want to return to Beijing will not be able to return.

"there is not a big shortage of postal workers. After all, it is a state-owned enterprise. During the New Year, about one-third of the workers will be on the job. The number of people returning to work in our area can now reach two-thirds. We are all from neighboring provinces. But Zhongtong had all their employees off two days before New Year's Eve, so they are short-staffed now,"Zhao said. According to his understanding, for those who just returned to Beijing, China Post requires employees to be quarantined at home for at least four days, while Zto requires a longer isolation period.

In a variety of part-time recruitment apps, it is easy to find nearly a week to release the courier recruitment information, many of which marked the "day of employment" , "Bao Chi Bao Zhu Zhu" and other key words, the monthly salary is in the range of 8,000 to 12,000 yuan. According to Zhao Zhixiong, the General Delivery Company to the temporary staff of the commission is 2 to 3 yuan per order, compared with the regular staff of 1 to 1.5 yuan is much higher. "But I don't see any new people on the site. They are all old employees. "

Even if construction starts smoothly, Zhao Zhixiong is not optimistic about his immediate job prospects -- as many of his colleagues have not returned to work, he has to help undertake some of the collection work in the adjacent areas, and most of the residential areas are off limits to express delivery vehicles, he can only wait at the gate of the district to collect more than 200 orders a day before, now it is 70 to 80 orders a day.

"In fact, I don't need to collect a lot of orders. Many of my clients sell teaching materials on Taobao. It was supposed to be the peak season for express delivery after the New Year, but now the school year has been postponed and their business is not good. I have collected a few days' income, at least half of what I normally get. " Zhao Zhixiong handled the most express items these days: Masks and disinfectant, gloves, shoe covers, which are many from abroad into the transfer of anti-epidemic goods, followed by vegetables and other fresh.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
On February 11, China Post delivered teaching materials to schools in Zhejiang Province. | PHOTO: China Post Official Weibo

After receiving the express mail, it will go through two stages of sorting and sorting. Zhao Zhixiong can also get masks, gloves and 84 disinfectants from China Post and Zhongtong daily, but he only takes one of them, "The front-line doctors are not afraid, I am a courier afraid of what, the resumption of work when it is time to pay attention to their own protection on the line, " he said.

Despite the income anxiety, Zhao gained a lot of corporate pride during the outbreak: "Wuhan Only China Post and SF express can send, SF express can send less than 3 kg of small items, we can send anything. "

Logistics warehousing: When to work to wait for the government notice

"every day there are customers in the group urging us to open the warehouse to get the goods, but the warehouse is sealed. When it can be opened, we have to wait for the notification from the park, and the park has to wait for the approval of the government, " Li told Yimagazine, China Business News, he works in the "storage and supply chain" Department of Shanghai Debang Express, mainly responsible for docking the purchase of debang storage services logistics customers, but is now under mandatory quarantine observation of the community.

"Some warehouse managers can't even get into the neighborhood, so they have to be quarantined in hotels, " he added.

According to Li Diwen's understanding, debang's Shanghai headquarters has already started construction, and all the functional departments that support the logistics of the system have resumed work. Those returning to Shanghai from other places need to be isolated at home for 14 days, during which they can work remotely. "colleagues back home in Hubei will not be able to return to work until the epidemic is over. "

Employees are required to have their temperature taken and wear face masks when they enter the campus, according to an online copy of the DEBON's headquarters campus epidemic prevention manual, which advocates bringing your own lunch box and eating at the booth, and that eating in convenience stores and restaurants is prohibited, for Dinner, head home to Florida -- the grounds will be sanitized after 6 p.m. In the office area, employees should be at least 2 card space between each other, use the meeting room must open all the windows, use a disinfection once. In order to prevent widespread infection, the entire campus will be closed, said air conditioning, director of the National Center for Disease Control and Prevention.

Before the quarantine, Li was able to go to the company's Front desk each day to get a mask and was told it was recommended for three days. Later isolated in the community, he mainly rely on playing games to pass time at home, occasionally to wechat group to calm the mood of customers.

"This is a very difficult time, we are all in a difficult situation, we have received orders, if Debon can not provide logistics support, then we have to choose another logistics business, now the order is our first, " a customer complained in the work group. Li diwen's own income is also directly linked to the volume of warehouse operations, these days of "royalty famine" since needless to say.

FOR THE SMOOTH START OF SF & JD.com logistics, he is not surprised: "I heard from my peers that the self-owned shops on the JD.com side have protective equipment in stock, while SF & Fung already has the special transport qualification of Chemical Transport and has a lot of protective materials in reserve. "

On February 10, Debon announced the resumption of "express delivery" through the wechat account, but Li's department is expected to resume work around 17 days. "Many of my colleagues are still isolated at home, unable to access the on-site operating system, and temporary workers are hard to find, making it difficult to function properly, " he said.

In order to fill the gap in distribution, "sharing the use of labor" approach is also used by the express logistics industry. On February 9, Dada, a distribution platform owned by the JD.com union, announced it would provide 35,000 jobs to the community in a flexible way, jd.com has opened more than 20,000 first-line jobs nationwide, including warehouse workers, sorters, couriers and drivers. At present, the enterprises involved in Yonghui supermarket, Bubugao and so on.

As for when this chain of events on the B-SIDE will end, I'm afraid it will have to wait until the epidemic is over.

(at the request of the interviewee, Li Diwen and Zhao Zhixiong were given pseudonyms.)
